## 8.2 Light Manufacturing

---

### 🟢 278. Textiles & Garments

**What it is:** Manufacturing clothing — woven, knitted, casual wear, formal wear, ethnic wear, sportswear, innerwear.

**Players:** Page Industries (Jockey license, big), Arvind Ltd (big), Raymond (big), Tirupur garment clusters (thousands of small units).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 + White Label 🏷️ | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📈 Extremely competitive — millions of garment units globally · 💰 Working capital for fabric, thread, labor · ⚙ Fashion changes fast · 👥 Bangladesh/Vietnam cost competition · 🌊 Cotton price volatility.

**Mistake:** Trying to be a generalist manufacturer. Specialize — "only women's kurtis" or "only gym wear" or "only school uniforms." Niche = efficiency = margins.

**One-liner:** Make garments — specialize in one clothing type for efficiency and expertise rather than making everything.

---

### 🟡 279. Footwear Production

**What it is:** Manufacturing shoes, sandals, chappals — leather, synthetic, sports, casual, formal, safety footwear.

**Players:** Bata (big), Relaxo (big), Liberty (Indian, big), Campus (Indian, big), Agra footwear cluster (thousands).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 + White Label 🏷️ | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Machinery + molds for each design · 📈 Brands dominate retail · ⚙ Each size needs separate production · 🧠 Comfort engineering · 📜 BIS for safety footwear.

**Mistake:** Producing too many styles. Start with 3-5 styles in one category (men's formal, women's casual, or safety boots), master them, then expand.

**One-liner:** Make footwear — master a few styles in one category before expanding your range.

---

### 🟡 280. Furniture Making

**What it is:** Manufacturing furniture — wooden, metal, modular, office, home, outdoor, institutional.

**Players:** Godrej Interio (big), Nilkamal (big), Pepperfry (online), Wakefit (Indian, D2C), local carpenters (millions).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 + Service Fee 🔧 (custom work) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📈 Unorganized carpenter market + IKEA entering · 💰 Raw material (wood, metal) costs · ⚙ Logistics — furniture is bulky, damages in transport · 🧠 Design capability needed for modern market.

**Mistake:** Only doing traditional carpentry. Modular, flat-pack, D2C furniture (like Wakefit model) is the growth segment. Invest in design and online presence.

**One-liner:** Make furniture — shift from traditional carpentry to modular D2C designs with online sales for growth.

