## 8.4 Chemical & Pharma Manufacturing

---

### 🔴 298. Pharmaceuticals & Drugs

**What it is:** Manufacturing medicines — tablets, capsules, syrups, injectables, APIs. India makes 20% of world's generic medicines.

**Players:** Sun Pharma (big), Cipla (big), Dr. Reddy's (big), Lupin (big), small pharma companies (thousands in Hyderabad/Ahmedabad).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 + Contract 📋 (CMO) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — regulatory approvals take years.

**Challenges:** 📜 CDSCO drug license, GMP certification, WHO-GMP for export · 💰 Clean room facility ₹5Cr-500Cr · 🧠 Pharmaceutical science + quality systems · 👥 US FDA inspections · ⚙ Batch failures cost crores.

**Mistake:** Starting without GMP certification. Without it, you can only sell locally and informally. Invest in GMP from day one — it's the license to operate.

**One-liner:** Make medicines — India's pharma strength is unmatched, but GMP certification is non-negotiable from day one.

