## 9.1 Material Recycling

---

### 🟡 328. Plastic Recycling & Pelletizing

**What it is:** Collecting waste plastic, sorting by type, washing, shredding, pelletizing into recycled granules for manufacturers.

**Players:** Dalmia Polypro (Indian), Banyan Nation (Indian, small — branded recycled plastic), individual recyclers (thousands).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 Pollution control license · ⚙ Sorting by type is labor-intensive · 💰 Machinery ₹10L-50L · 📈 Competing with cheap virgin plastic when oil is cheap · 🌊 Oil prices determine competitiveness.

**Mistake:** Not maintaining pellet quality. Manufacturers reject contaminated recycled pellets. Invest in proper washing and sorting.

**One-liner:** Recycle plastic into pellets — quality and sorting capability determine margins.

---

### 🟢 329. Paper & Cardboard Recycling

**What it is:** Collecting waste paper, sorting, baling, selling to paper mills for recycling.

**Players:** ITC Wellbeing (big initiative), local kabadiwallas (millions), paper mills.

**Model:** Arbitrage 📈 | **Revenue:** ⚡ Fast.

**Challenges:** 💰 Thin margins ₹2-5/kg · ⚙ Sorting removes contamination · 📈 Existing kabadi network competition · 🌊 Paper prices fluctuate.

**Mistake:** Not sorting by grade. Mixed paper = ₹5/kg. White office paper sorted separately = ₹12-15/kg. Sorting IS the margin.

**One-liner:** Recycle paper — sorting by grade turns ₹5/kg into ₹15/kg; the money is in sorting.

---

### 🟡 330. Metal Scrap Recycling

**What it is:** Collecting, sorting, and processing metal scrap — steel, copper, aluminum, brass — for re-melting and manufacturing.

**Players:** Individual scrap dealers (lakhs), Tata Steel (recycled steel), JSW (electric arc furnace), metal recyclers.

**Model:** Arbitrage 📈 + Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Shredders and balers ₹5L-50L · 🌊 Global metal prices swing · ⚙ Sorting mixed metals · 📜 Environmental permits for processing.

**Mistake:** Not investing in metal identification technology. Handheld XRF analyzers (₹5-15L) can identify metal composition instantly, enabling premium pricing for correctly sorted metals.

**One-liner:** Recycle metals — invest in identification technology (XRF) for accurate sorting and premium pricing.

---

### 🟡 331. Glass Recycling

**What it is:** Collecting waste glass (bottles, jars, flat glass), crushing, sorting by color, selling cullet to glass manufacturers.

**Players:** Individual glass recyclers, glass manufacturers (who buy cullet).

**Model:** Arbitrage 📈 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** ⚙ Must sort by color (clear, green, brown) · 💰 Crusher equipment · 📈 Glass collection is fragmented · 🌊 Transport costs (glass is heavy).

**Mistake:** Mixing glass colors. Clear glass cullet sells for 2x colored. Color-sorted cullet commands premium.

**One-liner:** Recycle glass — color sorting is the key to premium pricing; mixed cullet is worth half.

---

### 🟡 332. Rubber & Tire Recycling

**What it is:** Processing waste tires and rubber into crumb rubber, reclaimed rubber, fuel oil (pyrolysis), or rubber mulch.

**Players:** Individual tire recyclers, pyrolysis plant operators, crumb rubber producers.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 (crumb rubber, oil) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 CPCB approval for pyrolysis · ⚙ Tire shredding needs heavy machinery · 💰 Pyrolysis plant ₹20L-1Cr · 🌊 Output oil quality varies · 📈 Crumb rubber demand growing (sports surfaces, road construction).

**Mistake:** Running unregulated pyrolysis (burning tires in open). Produces toxic emissions, invites CPCB shutdown, and creates health hazards. Only operate with proper pollution control.

**One-liner:** Recycle tires — only with proper CPCB-approved equipment; unregulated pyrolysis is illegal and dangerous.

