### 🟡 335. Construction Debris Recycling

**What it is:** Processing C&D waste (concrete, bricks, asphalt, tiles from demolition) into recycled aggregates, bricks, and fill material.

**Players:** IL&FS Environmental (big), individual C&D recyclers, municipal C&D processing plants.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 + Service Fee 🔧 (debris collection) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 C&D waste management rules mandate processing · 💰 Crushing plant ₹50L-5Cr · ⚙ Removing contaminants (wood, plastic, metal) · 📈 Low awareness of recycled aggregates.

**Mistake:** Not marketing recycled aggregates to builders. Many builders don't know recycled aggregates exist. Demonstrate quality equivalence and cost savings to convert them.

**One-liner:** Recycle construction waste — educate builders about recycled aggregates; regulations mandate processing, creating guaranteed supply.

