### 🔴 337. Rare Earth Mineral Recovery

**What it is:** Extracting rare earth elements (neodymium, dysprosium, cerium) from e-waste, industrial scrap, or mining tailings. Critical for EVs, wind turbines, defense.

**Players:** Indian Rare Earths (PSU, big), Lynas (Australia, big), no significant private Indian players — huge opportunity.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 2-5 years setup.

**Challenges:** 🧠 Specialized hydrometallurgy/pyrometallurgy · 💰 Processing ₹5Cr-100Cr+ · 📜 Environmental clearance (radioactive thorium waste) · 👥 China controls 60-70% global processing · 🌊 Market prices volatile.

**Mistake:** Underestimating environmental challenge. Rare earth processing creates radioactive waste. Proper waste management is as important as the extraction chemistry.

**One-liner:** Recover critical minerals — strategically important, but environmental management is as critical as the metallurgy.

