## 9.2 E-Waste & Specialized

---

### 🟡 338. E-Waste Dismantling & Recovery

**What it is:** Dismantling electronics and recovering precious metals — gold, silver, palladium, copper from circuit boards and components.

**Players:** Attero (Indian, big), E-Parisaraa (Indian), Sims Recycling (global), authorized recyclers.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 (recovered metals) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 1-2 years for proper facility.

**Challenges:** 📜 SPCB authorization mandatory · 💰 Proper processing ₹50L-10Cr · 🧠 Chemical processing expertise · ⚙ Worker safety (toxic fumes, chemicals) · 📈 Informal sector does this illegally and cheaply.

**Mistake:** Cutting corners on safety. Illegal processing (acid baths, burning plastic) = pollution + health hazards + prosecution. Proper facility is non-negotiable.

**One-liner:** Extract precious metals from e-waste — "urban mining" is lucrative but authorization and safety are non-negotiable.

---

### 🟡 339. Battery Recycling (Lithium, Lead)

**What it is:** Recycling spent batteries — lead-acid (cars, UPS), lithium-ion (phones, EVs, laptops) — recovering lead, lithium, cobalt, nickel.

**Players:** Exide (lead recycling, big), Amara Raja (big), Attero (Li-ion, Indian), Lohum (Indian, small — Li-ion).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 Battery Waste Management Rules 2022 + EPR · 💰 Li-ion recycling plant ₹5Cr-50Cr · 🧠 Hydrometallurgical expertise · ⚙ Safety — Li-ion batteries can catch fire · 👥 EV boom will create massive future supply.

**Mistake:** Waiting for EV battery waste. Lead-acid battery recycling is profitable NOW (huge existing volume). Build capability and reputation with lead-acid, then expand to Li-ion as EV batteries retire.

**One-liner:** Recycle batteries — start with lead-acid (available now), build toward Li-ion (massive future wave from EVs).

