### 🔴 341. Circuit Board Recycling

**What it is:** Specifically processing printed circuit boards — shredding, separating metals (copper, tin, gold, silver, palladium) from non-metals.

**Players:** Attero (Indian, big), specialized PCB recyclers globally.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 🧠 Multi-step metallurgical process · 📜 Hazardous waste handling authorization · ⚙ Brominated flame retardants in PCBs are toxic · 💰 Specialized shredding + separation equipment.

**Mistake:** Processing PCBs without proper fume extraction. Burning or heating PCBs releases dioxins and furans — carcinogenic. Enclosed processing with filtration is mandatory.

**One-liner:** Recycle circuit boards — enclosed processing with fume extraction is mandatory; open burning is carcinogenic and illegal.

---

### 🔴 342. Solar Panel Recycling

**What it is:** Recycling end-of-life solar panels — recovering silicon, silver, aluminum, copper, glass.

**Players:** Almost no organized players in India yet — massive future opportunity as first-generation panels retire (2025-2030 onwards).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 (recovered materials) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — market just beginning.

**Challenges:** 📜 No specific solar panel recycling regulation yet in India · 🧠 Panel deconstruction technology still developing · 💰 Volume too low currently · 🌊 First wave of panel retirement starting 2025-2030.

**Mistake:** Building a large facility now when volume is tiny. Start with R&D and pilot processing. Build capacity when panel retirement volumes justify it (2028+).

**One-liner:** Recycle solar panels — early R&D now, scale up when first-generation panels retire en masse (2028-2030).

