### 🔴 343. EV Battery Second-Life

**What it is:** Repurposing retired EV batteries (still have 70-80% capacity) for less demanding applications — energy storage, telecom towers, street lighting.

**Players:** Exicom (Indian, medium), Lohum (Indian, small), global OEMs exploring.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 + Rental 🔑 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — EV battery retirement just beginning.

**Challenges:** 🧠 Battery diagnostics + repackaging expertise · 📜 Safety certification for repurposed batteries · 💰 Technology for grading retired cells · 📈 Volume still very low.

**Mistake:** Same as solar panel recycling — building capacity before volume exists. Start with pilot projects and partnerships with EV OEMs.

**One-liner:** Repurpose retired EV batteries — partner with EV OEMs now for future supply; volume will explode by 2028+.

