### 🔴 344. Medical Waste Processing

**What it is:** Collecting and treating biomedical waste from hospitals, clinics, labs — incineration, autoclaving, chemical treatment, shredding.

**Players:** Synergy Waste Management (Indian, big), individual CBMWTF operators, hospital-operated treatment facilities.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 (per kg/per bed contract) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 BMWM Rules 2016 — strict authorization and standards · ⚙ Segregation at source is critical · 💰 Incinerator + autoclave ₹50L-5Cr · 🧠 Handling infectious/toxic waste safely · 📈 COVID created awareness and demand.

**Mistake:** Not segregating waste categories properly. Each category (sharps, infectious, pathological, chemical) has different treatment requirements. Wrong treatment = regulatory violation.

**One-liner:** Process medical waste — strict category-wise segregation and treatment; COVID permanently increased awareness and demand.

