### 🔴 347. Catalyst Recycling (Platinum)

**What it is:** Recovering platinum group metals (platinum, palladium, rhodium) from spent catalysts — automotive catalytic converters, industrial catalysts, refinery catalysts.

**Players:** BASF (big, global), Johnson Matthey (big), individual catalyst recyclers.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium — PGMs are extremely valuable (₹25,000-1,00,000+/ounce).

**Challenges:** 🧠 Specialized refining chemistry · 💰 Assaying equipment essential · 📜 CPCB authorization · ⚙ Theft risk (catalytic converters are stolen for PGMs globally) · 📈 Niche market, limited players.

**Mistake:** Not having in-house assaying. PGM values are so high that even 1% error in assay costs lakhs. Invest in proper assaying or partner with certified assayers.

**One-liner:** Recover platinum group metals from catalysts — extremely valuable materials but requires precision assaying and specialized chemistry.

