### 🟡 356. Packaging Take-Back Programs

**What it is:** Managing Extended Producer Responsibility (EPR) compliance for brands — collecting and recycling the packaging they sell. Mandated by law for producers above certain thresholds.

**Players:** Saahas Zero Waste (Indian, small), Recykal (Indian, medium — EPR marketplace), Nepra (Indian, small), individual PROs (Producer Responsibility Organizations).

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 (from brands for EPR compliance) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium — growing fast.

**Challenges:** 📜 EPR rules are new and evolving · ⚙ Collection logistics across geographies · 📈 Brands seeking cheapest compliance, not quality · 🧠 Must prove recycling, not just collection.

**Mistake:** Offering collection without verified recycling. Brands need recycling certificates for compliance. Just collecting waste without proving it was recycled doesn't fulfill EPR.

**One-liner:** Manage EPR for brands — must prove actual recycling with certificates; collection alone doesn't satisfy regulations.

